Iris — Licensing
================

Iris consists of a core type-bridge library and an OS utility layer.
The core is GPL-2.0; the OS utility layer (src/os/, include/os.hpp)
is Apache-2.0 so it can be embedded freely without copyleft propagation.

Copyright (c) 2026 Iris Contributors.


Components
----------

  Core  (src/, include/ — except os.hpp)   GNU General Public License v2.0
                                            → https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/gpl-2.0.html

  OS utilities  (src/os/, include/os.hpp)   Apache License, Version 2.0
                                            → https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0


Iris Apache-2.0 Build Dependency Exception
------------------------------------------

As a special exception, the copyright holders grant you permission to
compile and link this library with Apache-2.0 licensed libraries that
are used solely as optional build-time dependencies — included only
through their declared public headers, enabled by a designated CMake
option, and not contributing to a separate runtime-loadable module —
and to distribute the resulting combined work, provided that:

  (a) the Apache-2.0 dependency is enabled only through the designated
      CMake option (e.g. -DIRIS_STDEXEC=ON) and is not unconditionally
      embedded into the core;

  (b) any modifications to the iris core (sources under src/ and headers
      under include/, excluding the Apache-2.0 OS utility layer) remain
      governed by the GNU General Public License v2.0;

  (c) you comply with the terms of the Apache-2.0 license for the
      Apache-2.0 licensed components, including preserving copyright
      notices and the NOTICE file where required.

The stdexec library (github.com/NVIDIA/stdexec, Apache-2.0) is a named
example of a build dependency covered by this exception.

This exception does NOT apply to derived works of the iris core itself.
A modified core must be redistributed under GPL-2.0; the exception
releases only the build-time inclusion of Apache-2.0 headers from
copyleft propagation.


Summary
-------

You may use, modify, and redistribute the core under the terms of the
GNU General Public License v2.0.  Any derived work that incorporates
the core must be distributed under the same license.

The OS utility layer (ls, ps, env commands and their type definitions)
is released under the Apache License 2.0 and may be incorporated into
proprietary or differently-licensed projects without restriction,
provided the Apache 2.0 attribution requirements are met.

OS utility source files carry the identifier:
  // SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0
